  "text": "Besides the cholinergic septohippocampal neurons, the medial septal nucleus and the diagonal band of Broca contain GABAergic neurons, which may contribute to the noncholinergic septohippocampal projection (Amaral and Kurz, 1985; Wainer et al., 1985; [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Fimbrial transections reduced the number of GAD-positive cells in the medial septal nucleus, providing evidence for the existence of a GABAergic septohippocampal projection (Fig. 6) . To test for the possibility that intraventricular injections of NGF prevent the disappearance of GABAergic neurons in a similar way as that of cholinergic neurons, rats were treated with either NGF or cytochrome c for 4 weeks and were taken for GAD immunohistochemistry.",
